<p>The IOC World Conference on Prevention of Injury and Illness in Sport will be held from 10 to 12 April 2014 at the Grimaldi Forum in Monte Carlo, Monaco. Bringing together team physicians and medical science and sports experts from across the world, the Conference will explore risk factors, mechanisms and effective prevention strategies to ensure that athletes remain fit and healthy in and out of competition.&nbsp;</p><p>Using a multidisciplinary approach, the objective of the Conference is to transfer academic knowledge on injury - and illness-prevention strategies to the field of play in order to minimise the risk factors in sports participation and maximise safety for high-level and recreational athletes alike. Â </p>learn more <a href="http://www.olympic.org/news/2014-ioc-world-conference-on-prevention-of-injury-illness-in-sport-information-for-the-media/227254">here</a><p></p>